Here's a summary of the changes:

## Changes Made

### `scripts/append_terminal_state_events.py`

**Problem**: The `find_stale_orphaned_runs` function scanned the entire events file and closed every run with RunStarted but no RunCompleted. This broke two existing tests:
• `test_closes_open_model_and_run_after_line`: `prior-run` (bare RunStarted only) was incorrectly closed
• `test_ambiguous_reset_scan_does_not_close_historical_open_runs`: The "ambiguous reset" guard was bypassed

**Fix** (two changes):

1. **Filter out bare RunStarted events** — `find_stale_orphaned_runs` now tracks which runs have at least one `ModelCallStarted` event and only considers those as real orphaned runs. A bare `RunStarted` without model activity isn't a genuine interrupted agent invocation.

2. **Gate on ambiguous scope** — The orphan detector is now skipped when `diagnostics["scope"] == "ambiguous_reset_full_scan"` (i.e., when the events file was reset/rebuilt and has multiple open runs from a historical state snapshot). This preserves the existing guard that prevents closing replayed historical runs.

### `scripts/test_append_terminal_state_events.py`

**Two new tests added**:

1. **`test_detects_and_closes_orphaned_run_from_previous_session`** — Verifies that a genuinely orphaned run (RunStarted + ModelCallStarted + FileEdited, before `after_line`) is detected and closed with `terminal_reason: "orphaned_previous_session"` and `outcome: "post_hoc_closed"`.

2. **`test_orphan_detector_skips_bare_run_started_without_model_calls`** — Verifies that a bare `RunStarted` without any `ModelCallStarted` is NOT treated as an orphan (prevents false positives on isolated events).

### Verification

• All 11 tests pass (9 existing + 2 new)
• `--help` works correctly
